# Per-Project Override — llms.txt Advisor

*Copy this file to `llms-txt-advisor.local.md` (without `.example`) in your project root and edit. The plugin's skills will read project-specific overrides from this file before falling back to the user-level practice profile at `~/.claude/plugins/config/llms-txt-advisor/CLAUDE.md`.*

*This file is meant to be committed to your repo (or gitignored, depending on team preference). The pattern is borrowed from `claude-for-legal`'s `legal.local.md` and `knowledge-work-plugins`' `brand-voice.local.md`.*

## Why this file

The user-level `CLAUDE.md` profile applies across all projects you advise on. This file scopes overrides to one specific site / repo. Use cases:

- You advise on multiple client sites and each has different IA + tech stack
- You want SEO routing rules specific to this project's keyword data
- You want to override the default site-type classification for an edge case
- You want to pin deployment-specific values (CDN, CI platform) without changing your global profile

## File precedence

Skills resolve values in this order:
1. **This file** (`./llms-txt-advisor.local.md`) — project-specific
2. **User-level practice profile** (`~/.claude/plugins/config/llms-txt-advisor/CLAUDE.md`)
3. **Plugin template defaults** (`<plugin>/CLAUDE.md`)
4. **`[PROVISIONAL]` fallback** if everything else is missing

